    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-11-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-11-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1">
                <head>1. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJ_1">Carter</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d1fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_CJ_1"
                            >Carter</persName> Library, National Security Affairs, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName> Material, Country File, Box 29,
                        Iran 11/1/79–11/14/79. Confidential. The memorandum was transmitted via
                        telegram WH92089 from the White House Situation Room to <persName
                            corresp="#p_WPJJR_1">Phil Wise</persName> for the President at 1141Z
                        (6:41 a.m. Washington time). <persName corresp="#p_CJ_1">Carter</persName>
                        initialed “C” in the upper right corner. He was at Camp David on November 4;
                        he returned to Washington the next morning.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-11-04">November 4, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Takeover of Embassy Tehran</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. According to reports from Embassy Tehran, an estimated 3,000 Iranian student
                    demonstrators occupied the Embassy this morning. Although they did not brandish
                    any weapons and professed to be engaged in a peaceful sit-in demonstration, the
                    students penetrated the security barricades within the Embassy and have
                    apparently taken the Embassy duty personnel hostage, tying their hands behind
                    their backs and moving them from the inner area of the Embassy. Chargé Laingen,
                    who was not present in the Embassy at the time of the takeover, was at last
                    report located at the Iranian Foreign Ministry. A Radio Tehran broadcast
                    confirms that hostages have been taken and that the demonstrators are demanding
                    the extradition of the Shah.</p>
                <p>2. State Department has established a crisis task force headed by Asst Secretary
                    Hal <persName corresp="#p_SHH_1">Saunders</persName> who is currently monitoring
                    the situation <pb facs="0051" n="2" xml:id="pg_2"/> in the State Operations
                        Center.<note n="2" xml:id="d1fn2">The Iran Working Group under Saunder’s
                        leadership issued regular updates and situation reports.</note> Efforts are
                    being made to contact Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_BM_1"
                        >Bazargan</persName>.</p>
            </div>
